SUMMARY:Give 'Em the Arrow Again!  Ladies Night at the Archery Range
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nI'm super excited to be able to offer another ladies' Archery night in Santa Rosa! If you've ever had a curiosity about archery\, this is your chance to find out more with a fun\, interactive lesson.\n\nWe have reserved a special event with the indoor range on a Wednesday evening. It will consist of a basic lesson\, and then we all get to practice shooting. Everyone will get ample time to practice\, as they have many lanes.\n\nThis event is focused on a less-competitive\, relaxed\, and entertaining atmosphere. All skill levels are encouraged. All equipment is provided by them\, and we will probably get about an hour or hour and a half to practice.\n\nI encourage everyone to bring a bottle of wine or a snack to share with the rest of the group (We usually end up with a lovely charcuterie and wine spread for everyone to enjoy). Closed toe shoes recommended.\n\nThere are 17 spots available\, guests welcome. The ladies' group lesson and event is $30 person\, paid to the range. Starting March 2025\, we ask that every attending member pay a $1 "slush" fund fee per event in addition to the regular fee so that we can build up our funds for club-related expenses\, which can be paid by Venmo or cash.\n\nPlease only RSVP 'Yes' if you are able to make it\, I will be doing a final headcount the day of the event. There is an attendance policy for all our events: if you No-Show to three events\, you may not attend events for the next three months. Please put this event in your calendar so you don't miss out or get dinged. A No-Show is when you are on the 'Going' list\, but do not show up.\n\nCheers\, and hope to see you there!
