DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260321T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260321T163000
SUMMARY:Corks Squared!  
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nWine Cork Art\n\nSAVE YOUR CORKS LADIES!\n\nWe are hosting a special event in March\, on Saturday the 21st at our old favorite\, K Squared Cellars. Local artist Tara Dickinson will be leading us as a group through creating a cork board masterpiece.\n\nEvent fee ($45) includes artist instruction and your personal cork art piece\, invite your friends to join us! Please bring all those corks you have saved and don't quite know what to do with. If you don't have any\, that's fine too. Let us know in the comments section so we can bring extra.\n\nVino is made available by K Squared for a separate fee *(by the flight or glass)*. The owner\, Andrew\, will be on hand to serve wine and entertainment.\n\nAbout the Cellars: After spending his first 9 years in the wine industry at Charles Krug Winery in St. Helena\, Andrew Moore developed a passion for crafting small lot\, premium wines. In 2010\, with a "the wine glass is half full" type of attitude\, Andrew's plans for owning his own winery began with a single barrel of Russian River Pinot Noir produced at home.\n\nIn 2015 K Squared Cellars acquired winery and tasting room space. That single barrel of Pinot Noir and a dream of having their own family winery was realized!\n\nAbout the Artist: Tara Dickinson is our artist and instructor. She has a background in fine arts and years of teaching expressive art labs to all ages. She enjoys sharing tools to help everyone feel comfortable in the creative process while learning new techniques. She moved to Santa Rosa in late 2021 after growing up mostly in FL and is loving the California lifestyle.\n\nWear your artsy clothing\, bring your thirst\, and corks for this 2-3 hour event.\n\n* Pre-payment *(via Venmo\, Zelle\, or PayPal)* is required for this limited availability event. **[PLS REGISTER/PAY HERE!](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdHYNFReJbhlLGQh0_wl4dEJZlF3E4nmEobQzB2W93XO7tz9g/viewform?usp=publish-editor)**\n* Maximum of 20 people\, **guests welcome.**\n* We suggest dressing warmly or in layers as the cellar will be a bit cold at this time.\n\nThe event starts promptly at 1:30 pm.\nPlease be a little bit early to get settled in with your wine and supplies. Tara will follow up with everyone who RSVP's 'Yes' to complete payment through her above link.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you all for this fun event in March!\nCheers!\n\\- Joleen and Dai
