SUMMARY:THIRSTY THURSDAY New Member Social for Sonoma County Women's Wine Club
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nThis is our regular club meeting\, held on the last Thursday of every month except for holidays and we are super excited! Come join us at 4th Street Cellars in downtown Santa Rosa. They have generously offered to host our monthly THIRSTY THURSDAY social for us.\n\nIf you are new to the area\, or just looking to get out of the house and make new friends\, this is the place for you. Welcoming to ALL new and (ahem\, old) members.\n\nWine is purchased by the glass for a set fee of $13/$14 per glass with the variety of white\, rosé\, and red wines offered through 4th Street Cellars which includes tip. Fees are collected at the venue by Co-organizer Daima Phipps via cash\, Venmo\, or Paypal. You are welcome to purchase wine separately if you choose. Starting March 2025\, we ask that every attending member pay a $1 "slush" fund fee per event so that we can build up our funds for club-related expenses\, which can be paid by Venmo or cash.\n\nThere is no food offered\, but you are welcome to bring an appetizer or snack to share with the group\, and many ladies do. We will have time to socialize while tasting in the room upstairs to the left or the outside patio if the weather is nice.\n\nThe space has a 25 person attendee limit\, but the list is open to 40 to eliminate a waitlist\, and guests are welcome! Please RSVP below only if you are able to make it\, we have an attendance policy: if you No-Show to three events\, you may not attend events for the next three months. Please put this event in your calendar so you don't miss out or get dinged. A No-Show is when you are on the 'Going' list\, but do not show up.\n\nSee you there\, ready to kickoff!
