DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T210000
SUMMARY:Give 'Em the Axe! Ladies Night at the Range in Santa Rosa
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nJoin us for an axe-throwing session to blow off some steam. I'm super excited to be able to offer a ladies' Axe-throwing night in Santa Rosa. If you've ever had a curiosity about this fun activity\, this is your chance to find out more!\n\nWe have reserved a group spot with the indoor range on a Wednesday night. It will consist of an introductory lesson\, and then we all get to practice taking turns. Everyone will get ample time to practice\, as they have many lanes.\n\nThis event is focused on a less-competitive\, relaxed\, and entertaining atmosphere. All skill levels are encouraged. All equipment and targets are provided by them\, and we will probably get about 1 to 2 hours to enjoy ourselves.\n\nI encourage everyone to bring a bottle of wine or a snack to share with the rest of the group (We usually end up with a lovely charcuterie and wine spread for everyone to enjoy).\n\nThere are 10 spots available\, guests welcome. The ladies' group lesson and event is $30 person\, paid to the range. Starting March 2025\, we ask that every attending member pay a $1 "slush" fund fee per event so that we can build up our funds for club-related expenses\, which can be paid by Venmo or cash. There may be standard liability forms to be filled out with the range. Closed-toed shoes are recommended.\n\nPlease only RSVP 'Yes' if you are able to make it\, I will be doing a final headcount the day of. There is an attendance policy for all our events: if you No-Show to three events\, you may not attend events for the next three months. Please put this event in your calendar so you don't miss out or get dinged. A No-Show is when you are on the 'Going' list\, but do not show up.\n\nCheers\, and hope to see you there!
