DTSTAMP:20260308T235824Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T160000
SUMMARY:Spring Fling Succulent Terrarium Class and Wine Tasting at Stuhlmuller Vineyards
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nSpring has sprung here in wine country!\n\nI have the pleasure of setting up a fantastic orb Terrarium workshop offered through Flourish Petaluma and wine tasting at Stuhlmuller Vineyards in Geyserville.\n\nIf you haven't been to Stuhlmuller Vineyards\, you are in for a treat. They are a spacious and unique winery open to the public\, with a tasting room and vineyards in Alexander Valley. They specialize in Pinot Noir\, Cabernet Sauvignon\, Zinfandel\, and Chardonnay. You are welcome to purchase wine outside of the tasting provided.\n\n**Get ready for a hands-on\, creative workshop where you'll dive into the art of designing and caring for succulents.**\n\nWe will be arranging individual terrariums\, chatting\, and sampling wine for 2-3 hours. You will have the option to choose from a wide variety of succulents\, colorful pebbles\, and vibrant mosses to personalize your own Orb Terrarium. Brandi\, the owner of Flourish will provide expert guidance\, care tips\, and plenty of hands-on support throughout the process. Everyone will be able to take their terrariums home after the event.\n\nThere is a minimum of 10 people needed\, a maximum of 20 people\, plus this is a Co-ed event\, so both men and women are welcome. Your spot is reserved by prepaying for your ticket through Paypal and the Meetup website.\n\nThe cost of the event is $86\, which includes the wine tasting\, our club fee of $1\, terrarium materials and guidance on succulents\, plus care tips. We are asking that you reserve your spot by prepaying just for the terrarium workshop\, which is $60. You can pay for the wine tasting there\, expected cost is $26.\n\nGuests are welcome\, they will need to pre-pay as well. I suggest you wear layers as we will be outside\, and sometimes the weather is windy or cold. Please allow extra time to get there\, the vineyard is about 5 miles from the Highway 101 exit at Lytton. We will confirm headcount about a week before.\n\nCheers to this fun succulent event!
